{
  "texts": [
    "CT employs the Leiden algorithm [77] as this was found to work best in experimentation but other algorithms can be used.",
    "The Leiden algorithm has a resolution parameter that is used to set the scale at which communities are discovered.",
    "Smaller values of this parameter lead to larger communities being found and larger values lead to smaller communities.",
    "For illustration, Fig. 1 shows the distribution of community sizes found when using a Leiden resolution parameter of 1.0 on the BBC News dataset.",
    "4CT returns 5 large topics that correspond to the five article categories of the dataset."
  ]
}